<T>__{cut to:}
<L>__{interior milady's house day}
<A>__{milady stands before a mirror, reaches for one of the many ivory combs that adorn her hair. as she places the comb we notice a small flower like tattoo on her arm. she pauses to admire her beauty, then to see the image of count de winter, now standing behind her, his eyes dark and cold. milady does not move from the reflecting glass, she smiles.}
<C>__{milady}
<D>__{count de winter.}
<C>__{count de winter}
<P>__{(as much happiness as the thought allows)}
<D>__{we found you.}
<C>__{milady}
<P>__{(eyes on the mirror)}
<D>__{yes. now that you have, what will you do?}
<C>__{count de winter}
<D>__{bring you back. to pay for what you did to my son.}
<C>__{milady}
<D>__{and if i resist...?}
<C>__{count de winter}
<P>__{(voice breaking with emotion)}
<D>__{i will kill you with my bare hands.}
